This paper discusses ethical challenges in data-driven dialogue systems, which are primarily used in natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques used in dialogue systems, such as reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also touches upon privacy concerns, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses safety concerns, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses reproducibility concerns, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
